Comment: Mudline core 1H had incomplete stroke and 15K overpull.  Recovery was full due to partial flow-in resulting in questionable mudline depth.  Decision was made to re-spud hole. PDR significantly off.
The bit and seal bore drill collar remained in the slips as the vessel moved 6 nmi to the next location.  The bit did not reach the rotary.
The hole was ended when several icebergs approached the location.  It was necessary for the vessel to pull out of the hole and let the icebergs pass.
Jet-in test to 16.3 mbsf only.  No coring attempted.
Hole 1254A ended with jettison of reentry cone.
Hole 1254B initiated when 1254A reentry cone was jettisoned
